---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Palchat – Bring ideas to life">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="space-y-8">
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-400">A calm home for product ideas</p>
        <h1 class="text-balance text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">
          Bring product ideas to life
          <span class="block text-base font-normal text-slate-300 sm:text-lg">
            without drowning in tools, feeds, or settings.
          </span>
        </h1>
        <p class="max-w-xl text-sm text-slate-300 sm:text-base">
          Palchat is a small, quiet site for thinking about how you build: short essays, simple mental models, and tiny
          tools you can use in the browser.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a
          href="#essay"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-slate-50 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-950 hover:bg-slate-200 focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-slate-200 focus-visible:ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-slate-950"
        >
          Read the featured idea
          <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>
        <a
          href="/about"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-slate-700 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium text-slate-100 hover:border-slate-500 hover:text-slate-50"
        >
          Learn what Palchat is
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-4 text-sm text-slate-300 sm:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="space-y-1">
          <p class="text-xs font-medium text-slate-400">Format</p>
          <p>Short essays & simple tools.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-1">
          <p class="text-xs font-medium text-slate-400">Noise</p>
          <p>No logins, no feeds, no notifications.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-1">
          <p class="text-xs font-medium text-slate-400">Audience</p>
          <p>Solo builders, indie hackers, and small teams.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="essay" class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 pb-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl space-y-4">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-400">Featured idea</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-50 sm:text-3xl">
        A dependency trap dressed up as efficiency
      </h2>

      <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 sm:text-base">
        Using AI and SaaS tools instead of people feels smart. You save money, you move faster, and you can serve more
        customers. The $1k vs $40k slide is easy to show in a deck.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 sm:text-base">
        But there is a quieter cost that does not show up on any invoice: the slow loss of understanding, custody, and
        resilience inside your own work.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/70 p-4 text-sm text-slate-200 sm:text-base">
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-50 sm:text-lg">What you quietly trade away</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-300 sm:text-base">
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold text-slate-100">Understanding</span> — work moves into a black box that you can
            no longer explain.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold text-slate-100">Custody</span> — your data and logic live inside rented systems,
            not in your hands.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold text-slate-100">Resilience</span> — when a tool changes or disappears, you may
            lose the memory of how your business runs.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 sm:text-base">
        The point is not to avoid tools. It is to remember that every dependency has a cost, whether or not it shows up
        on the invoice.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
